[[unpartei/PatternAlism|PatternAlism]][[http://google.com/search?q=PatternAlism|➜°]] ( devoted to Ray Kurzweil and beyond )

Energy cannot be created, nor can it be destroyed, it can only be transformed.

So at least energy is eternal.
Any pattern is a pattern of energy and probably has only <span style="line-height: 1.5;">a temporary (take billions of years as an example of temporary) lifespan.</span>

The whole (as a pattern of all patterns) is supposed to be eternal.
Each pattern is generated by the whole.

The whole creates itself endlessly in [[unpartei/AutoPoesis|AutoPoesis]][[http://google.com/search?q=AutoPoesis|➜°]].
The whole is [[unpartei/ImMortal|ImMortal]][[http://google.com/search?q=ImMortal|➜°]].

Feeling one with the whole gives some feeling of immortality.

